One person was killed and police officers injured when suspected al Shabaab militants ambushed buses in Lamu on Saturday morning. The buses were on their way to Malindi and Mombasa when the attack took place at about 11am. The attackers opened fire on the police officers who were escorting the convoy. Two of the vehicles were damaged during the exchange of fire. Police spokesperson Mwenda Njoka said they had not established the number of militants who were kiilled. Njoka added that more security agents were sent to the location - Nyongoro area between Gamba and Lango la Simba. "Immediately after the attack happened, a contingent of airborne and ground troops was dispatched from the Boni Enclave Campaign centre." "Swift action by the security team ensured the buses drove past the ambush area safely and without further casualties." Click here for the latest political news